{
  "texts": [
    "Deep learning (DL), a specialized area within ML, utilizes multi-layered neural networks to automatically extract hierarchical features from large datasets, enabling advanced pattern recognition and decision-making (LeCun et al. 2015).",
    "ML approaches with expert-informed hand-crafted features have attempted to address some of the issues pertaining to subjectivity and bias in the manual analysis of fossil image datasets (Sansom et al. 2010).",
    "Early ML applications in paleontology extended beyond specimen identification to include the classification and segmentation of fossil images.",
    "Algorithms like support vector machines (SVM) and decision trees have been used to isolate fossil features, such as differentiating between various skeletal elements or identifying specific morphological characteristics like cranial structures or vertebrae (Matthews et al. 2018).",
    "These approaches facilitate the instance segmentation of anatomical features, enabling detailed morphological analyses of fossil specimens, including the segmentation of bone structures or fossilized tissues, which is crucial for paleontological studies (Alghurair and Mezher 2020; Li et al. 2009)."
  ]
}